title: Album Page, "Sketch of Dormer with Slate Roof, Possibly Vannes, France", ca. 1888
medium: Graphite on thick off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric
inscribed: Recto, in graphite, upper right corner: 64; lower right corner: 57; to right of drawing: Note - the shingles on / small window do not / slant with roof of window / The slant is the same as that / of main roof.
description: Vertical sheet that has been cut down to make a horizontal rectangle depicting on far left side an elevation of a turret or pitched roof with a ball finial.  Below this is a small dormer that has been covered with slate or terracotta tiles.

tombstone.epitaph:
Album Page, "Sketch of Dormer with Slate Roof, Possibly Vannes, France", ca. 1888.
ca. 1888. Graphite on thick off-white wove paper tipped into binding with fabric. Gift of Mrs. William Greenough. 1943-51-230.
